berlegungen zum GAVI Rechtsprobleme des Nachtragsverteilungsverfahrens Ausgewählte Steuerrechtliche Fragen im Insolvenzverfahren Fragen des internationalen Insolvenzrechts, besonders des Insolvenzanfechtungsrechts  aThis publication is based on presentations given at the 4th Insolvency Law Symposium in Kiel (Germany) on current issues of German and international insolvency law. The following topics were addressed: the history of insolvency law; the insolvency court's supervision of the insolvency administrator; set-off options relating to tax claims; delayed distribution proceedings; insolvency and the English limited; insolvency appeals and the European Insolvency Regulation; international jurisdiction and conflict of laws.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aBankruptcyzGermanyvCongresses. 0aComposition (Law)zGermanyvCongresses. 0aDebtor and creditorzGermanyvCongresses. 4aInsolvenzrecht. 7aLAW / Bankruptcy & Insolvency.2bisacsh1 aBuchegger, Prof. Dr. Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForster, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLudewig, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPannen, Dr. Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRechel, Dr. Hans-Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidt, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSmid, Prof. Dr. Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmid, Stefan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTake, Dr. Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZeuner, Mark, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:d